There are 2 political stances: left-wing, right-wing, everything else is sophistry.

I'll tell you what to do: pick some candidate you like, just trust your gut, don't actually waste time reading their policies/stances etc. When voting day comes, if you have no important business, go and drop a vote for them. Simple as.

People who win the lottery and people who lose a limb are asked to rate their happiness from 1-10.

At the start, the lotto winners rate themselves 9 and the as-of-recently-disabled give their lives ~3

After only 1 year passes, both groups rate their happiness the same: "7/10"

Thread. A blackpill or a whitepill, depending on who reads this:

The average League-playing autist gets as much enjoyment out of life as the stereotypical Chad. This is how the brain works. It balances out and gets adjusted to your situation.

Consider the followin experiment:

Whether you're fucking 9s on the weekend, meditating in some shithole downtown group therapy place, grinding league games to get to Plat V, racking tons of cash as a salesman... it will not change almost anything.

There is no salvation in the World.

A worldly life will never be able to fully satisfy your soul, there will always be something missing. This is a very much intended thing, as is all related to the human body

You are not programmed for the glories and pleasures of the world.

You are meant for Something else.

You expect that once you reach your goals you will be happy, but you will simple get newer and bigger ones, until you are unable to achieve them after realizing your potential.

There are 2 roads to happiness:

1. Infinite expansion, the path of Caesar

2. Finding joy in Christ.

A grave distinction: in Christianity, weakness can only be shown from a position of strength.

When Christ let Himself be crucified, He could have turned all His enemies to dust, sending their souls to Hell. 

Meanwhile St. George, a mere man, was not afraid to face the dragon.

If you are weaker than your opponent, fight him.

If you are stronger than your opponent, spare him.

But, today, my friends, just as we were back in the catacombs, we are far from a position of superiority. It is not the time to show our meekness yet.
